#html.elem("details", attrs: ("class": "portfolio-item", "id": "project-hypar-map", "open": ""))[#html.elem("summary")[#html.elem("div", attrs: ("class": "company-logo"))[#html.elem("img", attrs: ("alt": "HypAR Map Logo", "class": "with-bg", "src": "./images/hypar-map-logo.png"))]#html.elem("h3")[HypAR Map#html.elem("a", attrs: ("aria-label": "Permalink to HypAR Map", "class": "permalink", "href": "#project-hypar-map"))[]]#html.elem("span")[November 2018]#html.elem("p")[First Place |#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch/qYet1ka1J3I", "target": "_blank"))[Demo]|#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://gitlab.com/ColoradoSchoolOfMines/facebook-hackathon", "target": "_blank"))[GitLab]| AGPLv3+]]#html.elem("div")[#html.elem("p")[This project won#html.elem("em")[First Place]at the Facebook Global Hackathon Finals at Facebook HQ.]#html.elem("p")[Read my blog post about this hackathon:#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "<!--TWYLA-HUGO:ref \"/posts/hackathons/2018-11-16-facebook-hackathon-the-competition\"-->"))[Facebook Global Hackathon Finals - The Competition].]#html.elem("p")[HypAR Map helps users navigate around unfamiliar locations by overlaying a map of the area using augmented reality. The map can come from any photo (for example, a fire escape plan) and is calibrated using an intuitive user interface. HypAR Map then uses simultaneous location and mapping to find and display the location of the user in the map in real-time.]#html.elem("p")[I worked on the image import functionality and worked with all of the members of the team to ensure that everything connected properly.]#html.elem("p")[HypAR Map was a hackathon project by#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://samsartor.com", "target": "_blank"))[Sam Sartor],#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://github.com/jhgarner", "target": "_blank"))[Jack Garner],#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://www.darling.dev/", "target": "_blank"))[Fisher Darling], and myself. We developed it during a 24 hour period at the Facebook Global Hackathon Finals at Facebook HQ in Menlo Park, CA.]#html.elem("details", attrs: ("class": "youtube-expander", "open": ""))[#html.elem("summary")[CS\@Mines Demo at Facebook Global Hackathon Finals]]]]

