#html.elem("details", attrs: ("class": "no-logo portfolio-item", "id": "project-datanium"))[#html.elem("summary")[#html.elem("h3")[Datanium#html.elem("a", attrs: ("aria-label": "Permalink to Datanium", "class": "permalink", "href": "#project-datanium"))[]]#html.elem("span")[October 2018]#html.elem("p")[Facebook Best Social Good Hack + 1 more |#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://gitlab.com/ColoradoSchoolOfMines/datanium", "target": "_blank"))[GitLab]| GPLv3]]#html.elem("div")[#html.elem("p")[This project won#html.elem("em")[Best Use of GCP]and the#html.elem("em")[Facebook Best Social Good Hack]award at#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://mhacks.org", "target": "_blank"))[MHacks].]#html.elem("p")[Datanium is a large-scale network of Raspberry Pis which allow for human-powered transfer of data between places with internet access and places which do not. In the Datanium ecosystem, there are two different types of users: consumers and couriers. Consumers request data, and Datanium ensures that couriers move the requested data to the Datanium Node closest to the consuming user. Datanium does this coordination using only SMS.]#html.elem("p")[I worked on the web frontend for requesting and uploading data to the Datanium nodes.]#html.elem("p")[Datanium was a hackathon project by#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://samsartor.com", "target": "_blank"))[Sam Sartor],#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://gitlab.com/robozman", "target": "_blank"))[Robby Zampino],#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://www.darling.dev/", "target": "_blank"))[Fisher Darling], and myself. We developed it during a 36 hour period at the#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://mhacks.org/", "target": "_blank"))[MHacks 2018]hackathon.]]]



