#html.elem("details", attrs: ("class": "no-logo portfolio-item", "id": "publication-dreams-of-flight"))[#html.elem("summary")[#html.elem("h3")[Dreams of Flight#html.elem("a", attrs: ("aria-label": "Permalink to Dreams of Flight", "class": "permalink", "href": "#publication-dreams-of-flight"))[]]#html.elem("span")[September 2016]#html.elem("p")[#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://www.rrcc.edu/claro/2013", "target": "_blank"))[Journal]|#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "./dreams-of-flight.pdf", "target": "_blank"))[PDF]]]#html.elem("div")[#html.elem("p")[I wrote this creative writing piece about Orville and Wilbur Wright and the first flight at Kitty Hawk for my Twentieth Century World History class in Fall 2013. I had written this piece for an assignment called#html.elem("em")[A Picture is Worth a Thousand Words]. We were tasked with writing an approximately 1000 word narrative from the perspective of a person in a significant photo from the 20#html.elem("sup")[th]Century. Later in 2013 I was published in the#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "https://www.rrcc.edu/claro/2013", "target": "_blank"))[2013 edition of#html.elem("i")[CLARO]], Red Rock Community College's Interdisciplinary Scholarly Journal. In May 2014, I#html.elem("a", attrs: ("href": "#presentation-dreams-of-flight", "target": "_blank"))[presented at the#html.elem("em")[CLARO]academic conference].]]]
